      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AYDEN'S WARRIOR (1) has some solid form under his belt and proved too classy last time to win by 1.5 lengths at Warrnambool in a handy 37.67 beating Amron Toy. Ran the fastest time on the program in his latest win. Expected to go well again. VODKA AND ICE (2) was out of in the placings when fifth last time but three runs back produced an excellent 41.52 win over 715m at The Gardens. Top win three back and can measure up again. APILLA (4) won again in an impressive display after leading them home to bring up eight wins in a row at Angle Park over 730m (42.79). Solid formlines coming through her last run. In sparkling form and looks the one to beat again. TEXAS PRESIDENT (7) can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
